data.chText: 成体系的；系统的；有条理的；有计划有步骤的
data.enText: done according to a system or plan, in a thorough, efficient or determined way
a systematic approach to solving the problem

data.chText: 力图摧毁那个组织的有计划有步骤的行动
data.enText: a systematic attempt to destroy the organization
The prisoner was subjected to systematic torture.
The search was carried out systematically.

simple_means.memory_skill: system 系统 + tic 有…性质的 → 系统的，体系的

value.def: Something that is done in a systematic way is done according to a fixed plan, in a thorough and efficient way.

example.ex: They went about their business in a systematic way...
example.tran: 他们按部就班地做生意。

example.ex: They had not found any evidence of a systematic attempt to rig the ballot.
example.tran: 他们没有发现任何证据证明有人企图全面操纵投票。

value.tran: 成体系的;系统的;有条理的;按既定计划的

example.ex: The army has systematically violated human rights...
She began applying systematically to colleges.
example.tran: 她开始有计划地向各个大学提出入学申请。

rootsaffixes.indicate: 表形容词，“有…性质的，属于…的，具有…的”
rootsaffixes.title: -atic, -etic, -tic
